# UI Design Guidelines

## Design System
- Follow the established color palette from the project requirements
- Use consistent spacing and sizing throughout the app
- Maintain a clean, modern aesthetic with ample whitespace
- Ensure all UI elements are accessible and easy to interact with

## Color Usage
- Background: Deep Space Gray (#333945)
- UI Elements: Light Elegant Gray (#F5F7FA)
- Main Text: Moon White (#E8EAF6)
- Secondary Text: Graphite Gray (#5C6B73)
- Accent/Interactive Elements: Mint Green (#76D7C4)
- Block Colors:
  - Coral Pink (#F1948A)
  - Sunny Yellow (#F7DC6F)
  - Sky Blue (#85C1E9)
  - Grape Purple (#BB8FCE)
  - Jade Green (#7DCEA0)
  - Terracotta Orange (#E59866)

## Typography
- Use the system default font (no custom fonts required)
- Maintain a clear typographic hierarchy:
  - Large bold text for headings
  - Medium weight for subheadings
  - Regular weight for body text
  - Small text for auxiliary information

## Animations & Interactions
- Add subtle animations for transitions between screens
- Include micro-interactions for button presses and selections
- Animate block selections and removals
- Keep animations smooth and non-distracting

## Accessibility
- Ensure sufficient contrast between text and backgrounds
- Make touch targets adequately sized (minimum 44x44 points)
- Include a colorblind mode option in settings
- Support system text scaling

## Screen-Specific Guidelines
- **Main Menu**: Clean, focused layout with prominent play button
- **Level Selection**: Visual distinction between locked and unlocked levels
- **Game Board**: Clear visual hierarchy with focus on the game grid
- **Settings**: Organized, easy-to-understand toggles and options
- **Leaderboard**: Clear ranking visualization with emphasis on top positions
- **Profile**: Visual representation of achievements and statistics